  <exercise label="ctp-recursion-17_fractals_11">
    <statement>
      <p>csp-10-3-1: What is the base case to create a snowflake through a recursive function?</p>
    </statement>
    <choices>
      <choice>
        <statement>
          <p>Draw nothing</p>
        </statement>
        <feedback>
          <p>Try again. We need to draw something to start. And a flat line will be the base case in our recursive function.</p>
        </feedback>
      </choice>
      <choice correct="yes">
        <statement>
          <p>Draw a line</p>
        </statement>
        <feedback>
          <p>Correct! A flat line will be the base case in our recursive function.</p>
        </feedback>
      </choice>
      <choice>
        <statement>
          <p>Draw a triangle</p>
        </statement>
        <feedback>
          <p>Try again. What does a triangle consist of? A flat line right?</p>
        </feedback>
      </choice>
      <choice>
        <statement>
          <p>Draw a line with a pointy bit</p>
        </statement>
        <feedback>
          <p>Try again. No pointy bit is necessary here. A flat line will be the base case in our recursive function.</p>
        </feedback>
      </choice>
      <choice>
        <statement>
          <p>I don't know</p>
        </statement>
        <feedback>
          <p>Try again. A flat line will be the base case in our recursive function.</p>
        </feedback>
      </choice>
    </choices>
  </exercise>
